debuggerPreference.comment: Whether debugging is to to 'just my code', or includes external package and SDK sources

debuggerType.comment: The type (Dart, Flutter, DartTest, FlutterTest) of debug session being started

debuggerRunType.comment: Whether the debug session is Run (without Debugging) or Debug

debuggerAdapterType.comment: Whether debugging is using the SDK or legacy debug adapter implementation

common.vscodemachineid.comment: An identifier provided by VS Code to relate coding sessions from the same installation together

common.extname.comment: The name of the Dart extension

common.extversion.comment: The version of the Dart extension

common.vscodeversion.comment: The version of VS Code running the extension

common.remotename.comment: The 'remoteName' from VS Code (such as 'ssh' or 'docker' for remote workspaces)

isDevExtension.comment: Whether the extension is running in development mode (this usually means running from source checked out from the Dart-Code repo)

showTodos.comment: Whether TODOs in Dart code are being shown in the Problems list

analyzerProtocol.comment: Whether the Dart analysis server is running using the LSP or Legacy communication protocol

formatter.comment: Whether the formatter is enabled, enabled-on-save, disabled, or set to something other than the Dart SDK formatter

flutterVersion.comment: Which version of the Flutter SDK is being used

flutterExtension.comment: Whether the Flutter extension is installed

flutterUiGuides.comment: Whether the Flutter 'UI Guides' are enabled and which kind of updates they are configured to use

platform.comment: The platform/OS the extension is running on

appName.comment: The name of the editor application (usually VS Code, but could be another editor that runs VS Code extensions such as from open-vsix)

dartVersion.comment: Which version of the Dart SDK is being used

workspaceType.comment: Which type of project(s) are in the current workspace (Dart, Flutter)

closingLabels.comment: Whether Dart's 'closing labels' hints are enabled

language.comment: The user's language as reported by VS Code
